her had started dating his colleague, Caroline. Now, she has asked Leonard (Stewart’s father) and Stewart to move in with her and her daughter, Ashley, who is at the top of the social ladder, while Stewart is almost at the bottom. His grades are great but his social skills are nil, but her grades stink and her social skills are great. </p>  <figure class=\"element element-image element--thumbnail\" data-media-id=\"abd5622f93117e2f1d1aa48f79198a0ac43c5d01\"> <img src=\"http://media.guim.co.uk/abd5622f93117e2f1d1aa48f79198a0ac43c5d01/0_0_315_500/315.jpg\" alt=\"fd\" width=\"315\" height=\"500\" class=\"gu-image\" /> <figcaption> <span class=\"element-image__caption\"></span> </figcaption> </figure>  <p>Their worlds collide, and Stewart tries really hard to fit into their new family. But the school’s biggest dude is ready to cause havoc when Ashley and Stewart catch his eye.</p> <p>This is a must read book that talks about family, friends, bullies and special bonds. </p> <ul> <li><strong>Buy this book at the <a href=\"https://bookshop.theguardian.com/catalog/product/view/id/281222/\">Guardian Bookshop</a></strong></li> </ul> <h2><strong>Want to tell the world about a book you’ve read?<a href=\"http://preview.gutools.co.uk/books/childrens-books/2011/mar/02/how-do-i-get-involved-guardian-childrens-books\">Join the site</a> and send us your review!</strong></h2>","liveBloggingNow":"false","shortUrl":"http://gu.com/p/4fbby","wordcount":"191","standfirst":"<p>‘This book is simply heartwarming. I didn’t want it to end and I wanted to find out what happened in the end at the same time’</p>"},"webUrl":"http://www.theguardian.com/childrens-books-site/2016/jan/07/we-are-all-made-of-molecules-susin-nielsen-review","apiUrl":"http://content.guardianapis.com/childrens-books-site/2016/jan/07/we-are-all-made-of-molecules-susin-nielsen-review","sectionName":"Children's books","elements":[{"id":"abd5622f93117e2f1d1aa48f79198a0ac43c5d01","relation":"body","type":"image","assets":[{"type"